caption: I normally leave awesome reviews for restaurants as I worked in the restaurant business while going to college. Usually I would never leave a bad review as I do understand things can happen. I had to leave a review because this is not the first time, or second or third that this store has really disappointed us. Tonight we ordered Uber eats at 6:05pm. We ordered the two 8 piece buckets as we had family and friends over and they are right down the street.  It was to be delivered at 6:45, then 7:15, then 7:40. At 8:00, we get a text from Uber that they have to cancel our ordered as they didn’t have enough chicken to fulfill our order. Wow!  Two hours later!  So we went to Chick Fil A instead!  On one other occasion, they only gave us 1 bucket of the two we ordered. On another occasion, we went through the drive through and ordered 1 bucket. They asked if we could come back in 20 mins and they would have it ready. Well 25 mins later, it wasn’t ready so we were asked to wait another 25-30 mins. My parents own a franchise. If I were the owner of this store, I would really try to find a solution!  You are losing lots of money!  What are your hours?  Shouldn’t you have enough chicken to fulfill orders during working hours??  I wish undercover boss would hit your store!  The employees are nice but what the heck?  How do you run a business?  How do you stay in business?  Close your store if you can’t run it properly. Get a better manager. This seems to be an ongoing issue with this store. Hope you make changes.

The service at this KFC was so bad that my wife and I found ourselves awkwardly giggling about it. We entered the lobby a few mins before it closed (the lobby, not the drive thru).  We had what we considered to be a large order, and thought it better to go inside rather than cause the drive thru to get backed-up. The guy at the counter ignored us for as long as possible, the made no secret of the fact that he was annoyed that we were in there.  He would just stop taking our order in the middle of it to just walk away.  He kept going to the lobby door to talk to someone outside.  He filled about half of the order then walked away.  After a few mins he was clearly irritated that we were still standing at the counter.  We had figured that some part of the order hadn't been cooked yet, as he didn't say anything to us once he decided that the order was filled.  We hadn't spoken-up yet because we didn't realize that he thought we had received all of our food.  He re-approached us with a serious "What's your problem?!" attitude and then tried to start an argument when we told him it wasn't all there.  We showed him the receipt (for the order he just took), then just went and got the manager.  To be clear -- WE were not arguing with or being rude or aggressive towards him at all -- he was just salty as hell and obviously felt like he had something better to do.  The manager begrudgingly corrected the order, but with the approach that my wife and I were the ones that screwed-up, not her horrible cashier.  She made no apologies for the situation.  The whole thing took around 45mins -- most of which was time being ignored by the cashier. I will never go back to that KFC again, and have been discouraging people I know from going there.
